# 07 : CODEGEN (v2) — no-LLVM, multi-backend
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ NO-LLVM COMMITMENT
  ∀ codegen-path avoids LLVM dependency
  Slang (400K LOC C++) = existence-proof production no-LLVM
  Zig-2022 LLVM-removal freed 200MB build-dep
  Enzyme-LLVM avoided : AD via source-to-source on MIR (§§ 05)
  MLIR used structurally (§§ 15) but dropping-to-LLVM-dialect NOT required
    — we drop-to-own-dialect + own-emitters

§ STAGE0 vs STAGE1+ BACKENDS
  stage0 :
    CPU : Cranelift (cranelift-codegen + regalloc2 + cranelift-object)
    GPU : rspirv for Vulkan/Level-Zero/WebGPU SPIR-V path
    GPU : DirectXShaderCompiler offline (stage0 shim) for DXIL
    GPU : spirv-cross for SPIR-V → MSL + WGSL
  stage1+ :
    CPU : owned x86-64 backend (§§ 14)
    GPU : owned SPIR-V emitter (direct from MIR, no rspirv)
    GPU : owned DXIL emitter (stage-2 target)
    GPU : owned MSL + WGSL emitters (stage-2 target)

§ CPU BACKEND — stage0 (Cranelift)
  flow : MIR cssl-dialect → llvm-dialect subset → CLIF (custom bridge)
         CLIF → regalloc2 → machine-code
         → cranelift-object → ELF .o (Linux) | COFF .obj (Windows) | Mach-O (Mac)
  ABI : SysV-AMD64 (Linux) + Windows-x64 + Darwin-AMD64
  SIMD : AVX2 base + AVX-512 opportunistic via runtime-CPU-dispatch
  target-features : ["+avx2", "+fma", "+bmi2", "+popcnt"] minimum
  debug-info : DWARF-5 (Linux/Mac) + CodeView (Windows)
  compile-speed : ~10× faster than LLVM (2s incremental achievable)
  runtime-perf : ~30% slower than LLVM -O2 (acceptable for stage0)

§ CPU BACKEND — stage1+ (owned, §§ 14)
  direct MIR cssl-dialect → own-MIR-passes → own x86-64 emitter
  own regalloc (graph-color + linear-scan hybrid per-fn)
  own instruction-selection tables
  own DWARF/CodeView emission
  closes 30% gap vs stage0-Cranelift

§ GPU BACKEND — SPIR-V path (Vulkan + L0 + WebGPU-portable)
  stage0 : rspirv module-builder
  stage1+ : owned typed-builder (3-5K LOC)
  capabilities declared per §§ 10_HW (Arc A770 baseline)
  memory-model : PhysicalStorageBuffer64 + VulkanKHR
  structured-CFG emission : MLIR scf.* → OpSelectionMerge / OpLoopMerge
  validate : spirv-val --target-env vulkan1.4 MANDATORY in CI
  optimize : spirv-opt -O (release) or -Os (size-constrained)
  NonSemantic.Shader.DebugInfo.100 : CSSLv3-source-line correlation (RenderDoc)
  VK_KHR_shader_non_semantic_info : debugPrintf inline any shader-stage

§ GPU BACKEND — DXIL path (D3D12, Windows)
  stage0 : emit SPIR-V → DirectXShaderCompiler -spirv mode → DXIL
  stage1 target : owned DXIL emitter (direct from MIR)
  signatures matched to D3D12 root-signature layout
  shader-model 6.6+ for mesh-shaders, ray-tracing, cooperative-matrix

§ GPU BACKEND — MSL path (Metal, Apple)
  stage0 : SPIR-V → spirv-cross --msl
  stage1 target : owned MSL emitter
  Metal-3 baseline (mesh-shaders + ray-tracing + cooperative-matrix on Apple-Silicon)
  argument-buffers for bindless

§ GPU BACKEND — WGSL path (WebGPU, Browser)
  stage0 : SPIR-V → Tint WGSL emitter (Google/Dawn)
  stage1 target : owned WGSL emitter
  WebGPU capability-subset : no-BDA (handle via binding-indices),
                              no-RT-pipeline v1 (ray-query optional)

§ GPU BACKEND — console stubs (NDA-gated)
  GNM (PS5) : stub + CI-skip on public-CI • impl under NDA
  NVN (Switch-2) : same pattern
  both read SPIR-V compatible-subset for portable-shaders
  platform-specific extensions via {Target<...>} effect + per-platform overlay

§ HOST-SUBMIT BACKENDS (R18)
  Vulkan-1.4   : ash crate (stage0) | owned FFI (stage1+)
  Level-Zero   : level-zero-sys (stage0) | owned FFI (stage1+)
  D3D12        : windows-rs (stage0) | owned FFI (stage1+)
  Metal        : metal crate (stage0, Apple-platforms)
  WebGPU       : wgpu-core (stage0) | owned impl (browser stage1)
  GNM / NVN    : platform-SDK (NDA)

§ SPIR-V EMISSION INVARIANTS (§§ 10 detail)
  module-section-order rigid :
    Capabilities → Extensions → ExtInstImports → MemoryModel →
    EntryPoints → ExecutionModes → debug → annotations/decorations →
    types/constants/global-vars → fn-declarations → fn-definitions
  forward-refs : only OpTypeForwardPointer (self-referential structs)
  PhysicalStorageBuffer64 loads/stores require Aligned operand
  OpConvertUToPtr / OpConvertPtrToU : 64-bit integers only
  NonUniform decoration on non-uniform-descriptor-indices
  LocalSize execution-mode for compute
  specialization-constants for workgroup-size tunables

§ FAT-BINARY (IREE-pattern)
  output .cssl-bin :
    [header]              magic, version, TOC, target-profile-set
    [host-obj]            ELF | COFF | Mach-O per-OS (may-multi-embed)
    [gpu-blobs]           SPIR-V | DXIL | MSL | WGSL array-of(entry, bytes)
    [symbol-table]        extern-C names + relocations
    [telemetry-schema]    R18 probe-metadata (§§ 22)
    [audit-manifest]      build-attestation signed (R16)
  runtime-loader libcssl-rt.{a,so} :
    detects-backend @ startup (Vulkan | L0 | D3D12 | Metal | WebGPU)
    loads-matching-blob, creates VkShaderModule / ID3D12PipelineState / etc
    initializes telemetry ring (R18)
    verifies audit-manifest signature chain

§ VALIDATION PIPELINE (CI)
  unit-tests : cargo test (stage0) | CSSLv3-test-runner (stage1+)
  spirv-val : every-SPIR-V-blob • MANDATORY
  spirv-cross round-trip : SPIR-V → GLSL → SPIR-V regression-detect
  differential-test : same-MIR → both SPIR-V + DXIL → compare-outputs
                      (when supported by Windows-CI runner)
  golden-frame-compare : render example, pixel-diff vs known-good
  performance-regression : power-draw, wallclock, dispatch-latency (R18)

§ HOT-RELOAD (§§ 13+18)
  dev-build : CSSLv3-compiler as-library in host-binary
  filesystem-watch → re-parse + re-type-check + re-compile affected
  swap :
    host-code : .so/.dll re-dlopen, function-pointer table re-seated
    gpu-shaders : destroy + recreate VkShaderModule + pipeline
    state : orthogonal-persistence (§§ 18) preserves engine-state
  production-build : hot-reload stripped, all-statically-linked

∎ CODEGEN
